{
  "texts": [
    "• The introduction of LEARN, a dual algorithm to UNLEARN that provides a new approach to adding new knowledge to the LLM without affecting its other knowledge.",
    "This paper presents the UNLEARN algorithm and demonstrates its performance in removing knowledge represented as tasks.",
    "Section 2 reviews the literature on Parameter Efficient Fine-Tuning, Machine Unlearning, and LLM Unlearning.",
    "Section 3 describes the three main parts of UNLEARN: subspace identification, subspace discrimination, and task removal.",
    "In Section 4, the performance of UNLEARN is tested over a large set of metrics and settings and compared to the current state-ofthe-art."
  ]
}